Hong Kong and mainland stocks kicked off the week with gains, extending last week's rally as reports said China and the US were closing in on a deal to end their trade war. The Hang Seng Index in Hong Kong added 0.51% to 28 959.59. The benchmark Shanghai Composite Index jumped 1.12% to 3 027.58 and the Shenzhen Composite Index, which tracks stocks on China's second exchange, rallied 2.21% to 1 599.48. 